SIMPLE: implore
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Implore
<hw>Im*plore"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Implored</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Imploring</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>implorare</ets>; pref. <ets>im-</ets> in + <ets>plorare</ets> to
cry aloud. See <er>Deplore</er>.]</ety> <def>To call upon, or for, in
supplication; to beseech; to pray to, or for, earnestly; to petition
with urgency; to entreat; to beg; -- followed directly by the word
expressing the thing sought, or the person from whom it is
sought.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Imploring</qex> all the gods that reign above.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I kneel, and then <qex>implore</qex> her blessing.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To beseech; supplicate; crave; entreat; beg;
solicit; petition; prey; request; adjure. See
<er>Beseech</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Implore</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Implore
<hw>Im*plore"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To entreat; to beg; to
prey.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Implore</ent>⟦br⟧

